BUSINESS ANALYTICS USING R

ABSTRACT

This project performs end-to-end business analytics using R. The analysis includes customer behavior, sales trends, and product performance to generate business insights and support decision-making.

CHAPTER 1: INTRODUCTION

Business analytics uses data analysis techniques to identify patterns, trends, and opportunities for improving business performance.

CHAPTER 2: OBJECTIVES

• Analyze customer behavior

• Identify sales trends

• Evaluate product performance

• Generate business insights

CHAPTER 3: DATASET DESCRIPTION

The dataset contains customer transactions, product information, sales quantity, price, and purchase month.

CHAPTER 4: DATA CLEANING

Missing values were removed and revenue fields were calculated.

CHAPTER 5: DATA ANALYSIS

5.1 Monthly Revenue Analysis

5.2 Product Performance Analysis

5.3 Category Analysis

5.4 Customer Spending Analysis

CHAPTER 6: VISUALIZATIONS

• Monthly Sales Trend

• Top Products

• Revenue by Category

• Customer Spending Analysis

CHAPTER 7: INSIGHTS

• Electronics generated the highest revenue.

• Laptop sales contributed significantly to total revenue.

• Revenue increased steadily over time.

• High-value customers were identified.

CHAPTER 8: CONCLUSION

Business analytics successfully identified sales patterns, customer behavior, and product performance. The insights can support strategic business decisions.
